pair.Prompt: What was the case of FTC v. TICOR TITLE INS. CO. about?
pair.Response: Response: FTC v. TICOR TITLE INS. CO. was a case about whether the respondents' conduct was entitled to state-action immunity under the antitrust laws in four states: Wisconsin, Arizona, Montana, and Connecticut. The case was decided by the Supreme Court on March 9, 1992, with the Court reversing the Court of Appeals and remanding for further proceedings. The case citation is 504 U.S. 621 (1992).
